step 1-- create the project 
step2--create a new repository in the github 
step 3-- go to project folder in the P.C
step 4--open GITBash from the folder(rightclick->click on Gitbash )
step 5--- command for GIt--->>>>>
                 1-->git init
                 2-->git add .
                 3-->git commit -m "any message"
                 4-->git status
                 5-->git remote add origin "paste link here"
                 6-->git status
                 7-->git push -u origin master 

by this the project will be pushed to Github account

    /// now the steps to deploy that project to heroku

go to heroku.com----->create a acccount---->click on NEW<>  (on the right hand top in the navabar)------>create new app---->fill the details --->click on create app----
----->click on github---->give the repo name ----->connect----->choose the branch ---->deploy Branch----wait---->VIEW
